<item>
            <title>[JCR-2449] Slow performance due to JCR-2138 (Prevent persistence of faulty back-references)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2449</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>In revision 782898, the following code was introduced:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
updateReferences() {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;for (Iterator i = local.addedStates(); i.hasNext();) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if (hasItemState(state.getId())) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This will try to fetch inexistent nodes from the persistence manager.&lt;br/&gt;
Depending on the persistence manager implementation, this is very slow.&lt;br/&gt;
I hope there is a way to avoid this call, or if not, speed it up.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
